Networking Related commands ::
===========================
> ip address show |or| ip a   are the advanced version of "ifconfig" (iproute2 => tool use for this)
> ip route → “Shows routing table” "Gate-way" , old one is "route -n"
> ping x.x.x.x -> check site is reachable or not (use icmp protocol)
> curl http://app_url	-> App not opening on the browser (work on application layer)
> nc -zv server_ip 8080 (work on tcp/udp)  |or| telnet server_ip 25  -> port is open or not on that ip ("telnet" was the older one only tcp )
> ss -an   => give details of all sockets  ( "netstat" is the depreciated command )
> ss -tulnp => tells you which ports are open in this vm using th ip and the apps using it
> dig www.xxxxxx.com => give you the dns ip (deep)
> nslookup www.xxxx.com => give you the Dns details only (fast)
> telnet <ip> <port> => check the servers specific ports are open or not (only for port testing) ne one is "nc"
> wget => to download the package from internet.
> nmap -sV 40.81.227.54 => which service and port are open or closed
> tracepath google.com => ping hit but app slow ( where the hop takes time )
> lsof -i :8080 => which process use this port.


FILE REALTED COMMANDS ::
------------------------

$ lsblk => To check Disk, partition, mount point in a tree format
$ df -h => which file system is how much filled
$ du -sh /var/log => how much the folder take space
$ find / -name "*.log" => find same type of extension
$ locate file.txt => search every where ( faster then find)


